sentences: Kirstin Taylor Maldonado (born May 16, 1992) is an American singer and songwriter.
Maldonado debuted her solo career on May 19, 2017, with the song "Break a Little" under the moniker Kirstin (stylized as kırstın™; ™ stands for "Taylor Maldonado").
Her debut EP, L O V E, was released on July 14, 2017.
She made her Broadway debut in 2018, portraying Lauren in Kinky Boots.
Kirstin Taylor Maldonado was born in Fort Worth, Texas, on May 16, 1992.
She graduated from Martin High School in 2010 and attended the University of Oklahoma, where she studied musical theatre on a full-ride scholarship as a National Hispanic Scholar.
In 2011, Maldonado was contacted by her high school friend Scott Hoying who wanted to put together a group for NBC's a cappella competition The Sing-Off.
On February 8, 2015, Pentatonix won their first Grammy for Best Arrangement, Instrumental or A Cappella for their Daft Punk medley.
On February 15, 2016, Pentatonix won their second Grammy in the same category for their rendition of "Dance of the Sugar Plum Fairy" which was featured on their holiday album, That's Christmas to Me.
On February 12, 2017, Pentatonix won their third Grammy for Best Country Duo/Group Performance for their cover of "Jolene" which featured Dolly Parton.
In January 2016, Maldonado performed the song "Somewhere Over the Rainbow" at the World Dog Awards in honor of the dogs who have played the role of Toto from the iconic story about The Wizard of Oz.
In February 2016, the a cappella group Voctave released the video "Disney Love Medley" which featured Maldonado and her then-fiancé Jeremy Lewis.
In May 2016, Maldonado, along with Grassi and Hoying, appeared in an episode of Bones.
On May 19, 2017, Maldonado released her first solo single, "Break a Little".
Her debut EP, L O V E, was released on July 14, 2017.
In 2018, Maldonado made her Broadway debut, portraying Lauren in the musical Kinky Boots alongside singer Jake Shears and comedian Wayne Brady:
Maldonado met singer and entrepreneur Jeremy Lewis in August 2013 through The Sing-Off, and the two started dating in October of the same year.
They got engaged on May 29, 2016 in Paris, France.
In 2017, the couple postponed their wedding to work on certain unstated "issues", eventually calling it off in October.
They have been dating since 2018.
